column5: THAT'S A BIG FISH.CONGRATS. SOMETIMES THROWING SOMETHING DIFFERENT LIKE A JIG IS EXACTLY THE RIGHT APPROACH.
Wow that's a pounder! I'd be happy with my day after that fish too!

beauty brown.  over 10lbs for sure.  i'm aware of a 20lbs brown that was caught in that same spot, which was caught while the angler was sitting his hard steel lure on the bottom chatting with a friend....browns are opportunistic feeds that will eat just about anything....  my favourite fish!
Wow seems like the browns are on fire!!!
Wow seems like the browns are on fire!!!  Tis the season..   Anything that imitates an emerald shiner is the ticket.   That brown is pushing double digits for sure.. 10-12lbs would be my guess.
Awesome fish.  Sometimes those big browns go on feeding frenzies and they'll only react to fast presentations like what you were using.  Congrats
